text:
as Ole said, `@@` indicates a div, there must be the corresponding CSS somewhere.

Another approach if, for instance, you want a bunch of elements which are all the same bar a few things (e.g. color) you could have the command insert raw HTML with style directly, here’s a toy example:

```\newcommand{\colbox}[2]{
~~~
&lt;div style="color:#1;"&gt;#2&lt;/div&gt;
~~~
}```
which you’d call `\colbox{blue}{hello}`

The next level is to make this a `lx_fun` or `lx_env` FranklinUtils is there to help (this is particularly useful for bootstrap elements) though the initial solution might be all you need :smile:
